public class First {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello world");
    }
}

Structure of above program:
every program in java is in terms  of functions and classes we will learn about them in detail later. 
Functions are blocks of code dedicated to specific purposes, classes are grous of functions.
every program starts from main() function and every line is terminated with ";" in java.
the above program prints out "Hello world" on the console screen. anything between "" is displayed as it is.
